An anonymous inner class will hold a reference to the this pointer of the outer class and will not be released until the thread ends.
It will hold the Activity and prevent its timely release.

In [DrugListActivity2.java](https://github.com/jclehner/rxdroid/blob/stable/src/main/java/at/jclehner/rxdroid/DrugListActivity2.java), there is a timed task.
It can be improved by TimerTask elegantly and efficiently.
```
timer = 
timerTask = timerTask(){
  run(){
  }
}
timer.schedule(timerTask,10,1100);

onDestroy(){
 timer.cancel();
}

```

When exporting local measures, it would be nice to have the possibility to export many ones in the same time.
We could copy the behaviour that is currently proposed to transfer several measures at once  (press on as many measures you want to export and then click on "Export" icon)

@nicolas-f @Picaut

@grmpl 

Hello, I found a problem with the app's UI design. At first sight, I thought the widget in the bottom right corner is related to copy or paste. But when I clicked on it, it saved the record. In fact, I think the function of this icon is different from the common icon I saw in other popular apps. As a suggestion, if you can design a more intuitive icon, it may greatly improve the user experience. Could you fix this issue?

